andromda_persistence:FinderMethod.andromda_hibernate_query: select p from PositionImpl as p join p.security as s where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and s.class = :type order by p.security.id
from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName order by p.id
from ComponentImpl where persistent = false

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select max(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) < time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
select s from StockOptionImpl as s join s.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join fetch s.securityFamily as f join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2.strategy.autoActivate = true order by s.id
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = StockOptionFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlyingId
from MeasurementImpl as m where m.strategy.name = :strategyName and m.name = :name and m.date >= :date order by m.date
from TransactionImpl as t join fetch t.security where t.type = 'BUY' or t.type = 'SELL' or t.type = 'EXPIRATION' order by t.id
from SubscriptionImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName and security.id = :securityId
select s.id from SecurityImpl as s where s.isin = :isin

from StockOptionImpl as so where so.underlying.id = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionType and (case so.type when 'PUT' then so.strike else -so.strike end) <= (case so.type when 'PUT' then 1.0 else -1.0 end) * :underlyingSpot order by so.expiration asc, (case so.type when 'PUT' then -so.strike else so.strike end) asc
from StrategyImpl where name = :name
select f from FutureImpl as f join f.securityFamily as sf where sf.id = :securityFamilyId
select f from FutureImpl as f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate order by f.expiration asc
select p from PositionImpl as p join p.security as s where p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.security.id
from StockOptionImpl as so where so.underlying.id = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionType order by so.expiration asc, abs(:underlyingSpot - so.strike) asc
from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and p.security.securityFamily.id = :securityFamilyId order by p.security.id
from CombinationImpl where persistent = false
from PositionImpl as p where p.security.id = :securityId and p.quantity != 0 order by p.id
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join c.underlying as ul join c.subscriptions as s where s.strategy.name = :strategyName and ul.id = :underlyingId
from TransactionImpl as t where t.strategy.name = :strategyName order by t.dateTime desc
select * from tick as t where t.security_fk = :securityId and date_time <= :date and date_time > DATE_SUB(:date, INTERVAL 1 MINUTE) order by t.date_time limit 1
from SubscriptionImpl where strategy.name = :strategyName order by security.id
from TickImpl as t left join fetch t.security as s left join fetch s.underlying as ul where t.id in (:ids) order by t.dateTime asc
select s from StrategyImpl as s where s.autoActivate = true order by s.id
from DefaultOrderPreferenceImpl where securityFamily.id = :securityFamilyId and strategy.name = :strategyName
from MeasurementImpl as m where m.strategy.name = :strategyName and m.name = :name and m.date = :date
from PortfolioValueImpl where dateTime > :minDate and strategy.name = :strategyName
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join s.subscriptions as su where su != null and s.id = :securityId
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su where su.strategy.name = :strategyName and s.id = :securityId
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join s.components as c join s.subscriptions as su where su.strategy.name = :strategyName and c.security.id = :securityId
from PropertyImpl where persistent = false
from MeasurementImpl as m where m.strategy.name = :strategyName and m.name = :name and m.date <= :date order by m.date desc
from FutureImpl f where f.securityFamily.id = :futureFamilyId and f.expiration = :expirationDate
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id = :id
from SecurityImpl as s where s.isin = :isin
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su where su.strategy.name = :strategyName and s.class = :type
select t from TickImpl as t join t.security.subscriptions as s where s != null and t.dateTime > :startDate and t.dateTime < :endDate order by t.dateTime
select sum(t.quantity) from TransactionImpl as t where t.security.id = :securityId and t.dateTime < :date group by t.security.id
select distinct s.expiration from TickImpl as t join t.security as s where t.dateTime = :dateTime and s.class = StockOptionImpl and s.underlying.id = :underlyingId order by s.expiration
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c left join c.strategy as s where or s.name = :strategyName

select t1.id from tick as t1 join (select min(id) as id from tick where date_time < :maxDate and security_fk = :securityId and time(date_time) > time(:time) group by date(date_time) ) as t2 on t1.id = t2.id order by t1.date_time asc
select s from SecurityImpl as s join s.subscriptions as su where su != null
from ForexImpl as f where f.baseCurrency = :baseCurrency and f.securityFamily.currency = :transactionCurrency
from TransactionImpl as t where t.type = 'CREDIT' or t.type = 'DEBIT' or t.type = 'INTREST_PAID' or t.type = 'INTREST_RECEIVED' or t.type = 'FEES' or t.type = 'REFUND' order by t.id
from SubscriptionImpl as s where s.strategy.autoActivate = true and s.security.id = :securityId order by s.id
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su where su.strategy.name = :strategyName
from SecurityImpl as s where s.id in (:ids) order by s.id
from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 order by p.security.id
select t from ImpliedVolatilityImpl as i, TickImpl as t where t.security = i and t.dateTime = :date and i.underlying = :underlying and i.duration = :duration order by i.moneyness desc
select p from PositionImpl as p join p.security as s where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and s.class = ForexImpl order by p.security.id
from SubscriptionImpl as s where s.strategy.autoActivate = true order by s.id

select s2 from SubscriptionImpl as s2 join s2.security as s where s2.strategy.name = :strategyName and s not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0) and s.class = :type
select distinct c from CombinationImpl as c join c.subscriptions as s where s.strategy.name = :strategyName
from TickImpl as t where t.security.id = :securityId and t.dateTime <= :maxDate order by t.dateTime desc
select distinct s from StockOptionImpl as s join s.subscriptions as s2 where s2 != null order by s.id
from SecurityImpl as s left join fetch s.underlying as ul join fetch s.securityFamily as f where s.id = :id
from StrategyImpl as st join fetch st.cashBalances where st.name = :name
from PositionImpl as p where p.id = :id
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join s.components as c join s.subscriptions as su join c.security as se where su.strategy.name = :strategyName and se.class = :type and c.quantity = 0

select so from StockOptionImpl as so, TickImpl as t where so.id = t.security.id and so.underlying.id = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionType and t.dateTime = :date and (case so.type when 'PUT' then so.strike else -so.strike end) <= (case so.type when 'PUT' then 1.0 else -1.0 end) * :underlyingSpot order by so.expiration asc, (case so.type when 'PUT' then -so.strike else so.strike end) asc
select p from ExpirableI as e join e.positions as p where p.quantity != 0 and e.expiration <= :currentTime

select so from StockOptionImpl as so, TickImpl as t where so.id = t.security.id and so.underlying.id = :underlyingId and so.expiration >= :targetExpirationDate and so.type = :optionType and t.dateTime = :date order by so.expiration asc, abs(:underlyingSpot - so.strike) asc
from TransactionImpl as t order by t.dateTime desc
select distinct c from ComponentImpl as c join fetch c.security as s join fetch c.parentSecurity as p join p.subscriptions as su where su != null
from CashBalanceImpl as c where c.strategy.name = :strategyName

select new TransactionSummaryVO( t.security.id, t.strategy.name, sum(t.quantity)) from TransactionImpl as t where t.security != null group by t.security.id, t.strategy.name having sum(t.quantity) != 0
from PositionImpl as p where p.quantity != 0 order by p.security.id
select distinct s from SecurityImpl as s join s.components as c join s.subscriptions as su join c.security as se where su.strategy.name = :strategyName and se.class = :type
select distinct f from FutureImpl as f join f.subscriptions as s where s != null order by f.id
select p from PositionImpl as p join p.security.securityFamily as f where p.quantity != 0 and f.tradeable = true order by p.security.id
select f from SecurityImpl as s join s.derivedSecurityFamilies as f where f.class = FutureFamilyImpl and s.id = :underlyingId
from SecurityImpl as s where s.symbol = :symbol

select cast(right(UUID_SHORT(),9) as unsigned) as id, t.security_fk, date(t.date_time) as date_time, cast(substring_index(group_concat((case f.tradeable when true then (t.bid + t.ask) / 2 else t.last end) order by t. date_time),',',1) as decimal (12,5)) as open, max(case f.tradeable when true then (t.bid + t.ask) / 2 else t.last end) as high, min(case f.tradeable when true then (t.bid + t.ask) / 2 else t.last end) as low, cast(substring_index(group_concat((case f.tradeable when true then (t.bid + t.ask) / 2 else t.last end) order by t.date_time desc),',',1) as decimal (12,5)) as close, sum(t.vol) as vol, 0 as open_interest, 0 as adj_close from tick as t join security as s on t.security_fk = s.id join security_family as f on s.security_family_fk = f.id where t.security_fk = :securityId and date_time >= :fromDate and date_time <= :toDate group by t.security_fk, date(t.date_time)
from SubscriptionImpl as s where s.strategy.name = :strategyName and s.security not in ( select p.security from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0)
select distinct c.currency from CashBalanceImpl as c
from SecurityImpl as s where s.ric = :ric
from SubscriptionImpl where persistent = false
from TickImpl as t join fetch t.security as s where t.dateTime = :date and s.underlying = :underlying and s.type = :type and s.expiration = :expiration order by s.strike
from PositionImpl as p where p.strategy.name = :strategyName and p.quantity != 0 and p.security.securityFamily.tradeable = true order by p.security.id
select distinct dateTime from TickImpl
from OrderPreferenceImpl where name = :name
from TickImpl as s where s.security.id = :securityId order by s.dateTime
from PositionImpl as p where p.security.id = :securityId and p.strategy.name = :strategyName
